### Phase 1 — Backend

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Additive only. No existing model, serializer, or view file is touched — new code is appended.

#### [NEW] `StorefrontConfig` model — appended to `D:\Shopdibz\Backend\store\models.py`

```python
class StorefrontConfig(models.Model):
    """
    Stores draft + live storefront theme config for a store.
    Separate from Store.themes (palette-only field, legacy).
    Gated to Gold and Platinum plan stores only.
    """
    store        = models.OneToOneField(Store, on_delete=models.CASCADE, related_name="storefront_config")
    draft        = models.JSONField(default=dict, blank=True)
    live         = models.JSONField(default=dict, blank=True)
    last_saved   = models.DateTimeField(auto_now=True)
    published_at = models.DateTimeField(null=True, blank=True)

    class Meta:
        db_table = "store_storefront_config"

    def __str__(self):
        return f"{self.store.name} storefront config"
```

Zero impact on the existing `store` table. A migration is required (`makemigrations store`).

#### [MODIFY] `GetStoreInfoBuyerSerializer` — in `D:\Shopdibz\Backend\store\api\serializers.py`

Add **one new field** to the existing buyer serializer:

```python
storefrontConfig = serializers.SerializerMethodField("get_storefront_config")

def get_storefront_config(self, store):
    try:
        return store.storefront_config.live or {}
    except StorefrontConfig.DoesNotExist:
        return {}
```

This is the **only modification to an existing file**. It is purely additive — a new read-only field on an existing serializer. No existing field is changed.

> [!NOTE]
> The field returns `{}` if no config exists, so all existing stores continue to work without any change.

#### [NEW] 2 Brand Hub API views — appended to `D:\Shopdibz\Backend\store\api\views.py`

1. **`GET/POST /store/storefront/config/manage/`** — Authenticated. Gold + Platinum only (`plan in ['G', 'P']`). `GET` returns `{draft, live, published_at}`. `POST` saves to the `draft` field only.
2. **`POST /store/storefront/config/publish/`** — Authenticated. Gold + Platinum only. Validates the current `draft` against the theme's required-fields list. If valid → copies `draft` to `live`, sets `published_at`, returns success. If invalid → returns `{ "missing": ["hero.desktop_url"] }`.

Both views are new classes appended **at the end of the file only**. Per `.codexrules`.

#### [NEW] 2 URL patterns — bottom of `D:\Shopdibz\Backend\store\api\urls.py`

